01:01.739 --> 01:03.674
Living the dream, right?

01:04.675 --> 01:08.209
A big, beautiful,
murderous deathy dream.

01:08.456 --> 01:10.189
Unless, of course, the cops show up.

01:11.300 --> 01:12.475
Des, it's been a week.

01:12.500 --> 01:13.699
We haven't heard anything.

01:14.941 --> 01:17.479
Well, I guess we live to
fight another day then.

01:23.621 --> 01:25.720
There's something very liberating

01:25.745 --> 01:29.125
about just lying back

01:29.785 --> 01:32.028
and waving your arms and legs around,

01:32.426 --> 01:34.196
forgetting everything except

01:35.128 --> 01:37.847
the cold air on your skin.

01:39.777 --> 01:41.308
Leaving your mark.

01:43.207 --> 01:45.112
At least until the snow falls again.

01:45.137 --> 01:48.177
I must say, that's one of
our stranger last requests.

01:53.817 --> 01:56.951
- Are you comfortable?
- Perfection.

01:57.211 --> 01:58.854
I mean, apart from the cancer.

02:13.523 --> 02:16.638
It smells like fresh baked
bread and a hint of limestone.

02:16.674 --> 02:18.740
Sounds like you know your champagne.

02:18.954 --> 02:20.655
I've had a few of these in my day.

02:23.868 --> 02:25.700
Time for my dying wish.

02:27.542 --> 02:30.176
Your baby. Who's the father?

02:32.005 --> 02:33.470
Did you love him at least?

02:34.018 --> 02:37.592
Now, now, Martha, I'm
starting to think you're stalling.

02:37.627 --> 02:40.595
- Are you having second thoughts?
- Not at all.

02:42.833 --> 02:46.703
The beauty of how I lived my life...

02:47.896 --> 02:51.464
I... made my own choices
all the way through.

02:51.489 --> 02:53.761
I... I travelled.

02:53.786 --> 02:56.713
I... slept with a thousand men.

02:58.715 --> 03:00.382
I did whatever I wanted.

03:02.015 --> 03:04.382
And I'm getting to do this my way too.

03:07.287 --> 03:08.408
It was...

03:08.763 --> 03:10.669
the fullest life

03:11.435 --> 03:12.481
in the world.

